$ scripts/tags.sh

code {
$ tags.sh <mode>
code }

 `<mode>` is one of
   • `tags`
   • `gtags`
   • `cscope`
   • `TAGS`

The script can be invoked via `make`, for example with
code {
$ make cscope O=. SRCARCH=xxxx COMPILED_SOURCE=compiled
code }

sa:

  → Linux/kernel/compilation/make#linux-make-targets[Specific `make` targets] to create tag files.

  → Linux/kernel/source/scripts[`scripts/`]
